Adapter behavior (per F.6 spec):
  ✓ Adapter object: toolkit='googledrive', events=[
      'GOOGLEDRIVE_FILE_CREATED_TRIGGER',
      'GOOGLEDRIVE_NEW_FILE_MATCHING_QUERY_TRIGGER'
    ]
  ✓ initialState: anchors last_seen_modified at now() + empty
    last_seen_file_ids so the first poll doesn't dump back-catalog.
  ✓ poll: calls Composio /tools/execute/GOOGLEDRIVE_LIST_FILES with
    q built by buildDriveQuery:
      - Always: `modifiedTime > '<last_seen>'` + `trashed = false`
      - mimeType (string OR array OR-grouped + parenthesized)
      - parents (single 'X' in parents, array OR-grouped)
      - freeform query wrapped in parens and ANDed in
    plus { page_size: 100, fields: '...', order_by: 'modifiedTime' }.
  ✓ Pagination: iterates nextPageToken pages (cap 50, 100 files/page).
    Dedupes within a single sweep by file.id via Set.
  ✓ id-aware boundary drop (mirrors F.5 fix):
      - Drives q-language uses strict `>` on modifiedTime, but
        same-ms ties can still occur after Drive's internal rounding.
      - State tracks last_seen_file_ids; an event is dropped only if
        modifiedTime === lastSeen AND id is in the prior set.
      - When new high-water equals prior, merges old + new boundary
        ids so subsequent polls keep dedup intact.
  ✓ Payload shape: { file, file_id, mime_type, modified_time }.
    cron-kicker's default buildInputs wraps in
    { event: { type, toolkit, ...payload } } so the agent sees
    file metadata under env.event.{file, file_id, mime_type,
    modified_time}.
  ✓ Defensive recovery on missing last_seen_modified: silent
    re-baseline at now(), zero events, NO fetch call.
  ✓ HTTP errors + successful=false envelope both throw cleanly so
    the cron-kicker circuit breaker counts them.

